  "prompt": "What is the procedure for 48 days Lord Murugan fasting?",
  "response": "The 48-day fasting ritual dedicated to Lord Murugan, known as \"Kanda Shashti Vratam\" or \"Karthikai Vratam,\" is observed by devotees to seek the blessings of Lord Murugan for spiritual growth, protection, and the removal of obstacles. This fast usually culminates on the day of **Kanda Shashti**, which falls in the Tamil month of **Aippasi** (October\u2013November). Here\u2019s a general procedure for observing the 48-day fast:\n\n---\n\n### **Preparation and Intention**\n1. **Sankalpa (Resolution):**  \n   Begin with a sincere intention to undertake the fast for spiritual purification and devotion to Lord Murugan.\n2. **Seek Blessings:**  \n   Visit a Murugan temple or pray at home to seek the Lord's blessings before starting the fast.\n\n---\n\n### **Firitual Details**\n1. **Duration:**  \n   The fast begins 48 days before Kanda Shashti and is observed daily until the final day.\n2. **Dietary Restrictions:**  \n   - Devotees typically follow a **sattvic diet** (pure vegetarian food) during the fast.  \n   - Avoid onions, garlic, meat, fish, eggs, and alcohol.  \n   - Some devotees may choose to eat only one meal a day or consume only fruits, milk, and light meals.\n3. **Daily Practices:**  \n   - **Morning Rituals:** Wake up early, take a bath, and wear clean clothes.  \n   - **Puja:** Perform daily prayers to Lord Murugan. Chant hymns like **Kanda Shashti Kavacham**, **Subramanya Bhujangam**, or **Skanda Shashti Kavasam**.  \n   - **Archanai:** Offer flowers, fruits, and incense to Lord Murugan.  \n   - **Lighting Lamps:** Light oil lamps or ghee lamps in the evening.  \n4. **Observing Purity:**  \n   Maintain mental and physical purity by avoiding negative thoughts, anger, and harmful actions.\n\n---\n\n### **Special Observances During the Fast**\n- **Krittika Nakshatra:**  \n   Worship Lord Murugan on days when the Krittika star (Nakshatra) is present, as it is associated with Him.  \n- **Tuesdays and Sundays:**  \n   These days are considered especially auspicious for Lord Murugan. Devotees may perform extra prayers or visit temples on these days.\n\n---\n\n### **Final Day: Kanda Shashti**\n1. **Complete Fast:**  \n   On the day of Kanda Shashti, some devotees observe a strict fast without food or water (nirjala vratam).  \n2. **Theertham:**  \n   Visit a Murugan temple to receive theertham (holy water) and prasadam.  \n3. **Soorasamharam:**  \n   If possible, attend the **Soorasamharam** ritual, which reenacts Lord Murugan's victory over the demon Soorapadman.  \n4. **Breaking the Fast:**  \n   Break the fast after the evening puja, typically with a simple sattvic meal.\n\n---\n\n### **Spiritual Benefits**\nThe 48-day fast is believed to:\n- Purify the mind and body.  \n- Strengthen devotion to Lord Murugan.  \n- Remove obstacles and bring success in endeavors.  \n- Grant spiritual growth and inner peace.\n\n---\n\nDevotees often customize the fasting rules based on their health and capacity. It is important to maintain sincerity and devotion throughout the observance. If you have health concerns, consult a doctor or spiritual guide before undertaking the fast.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
